y-to-day lives. By helping to increase the distance between cisgender and transgender people, Miller argues, these films make it more difficult for cisgender people to understand the experiences of transgender people and for transgender people to fully participate in public life. The book concludes with suggestions for improving transgender representation in film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aGender identity in motion pictures. 0aTransgender people in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849201840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438492018423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438492018/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles